==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Proselytism
<hw>Pros"e*ly*tism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>pros⟦eacute⟧lytisme</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or
practice of proselyting; the making of converts to a religion or a
religious sect, or to any opinion, system, or party.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They were possessed of a spirit of <qex>proselytism</qex> in the
most fanatical degree.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Conversion to a religion, system, or
party.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Proselytize</ent>⟦br⟧
